            "answer_text": "At a point of time,when Hindu Muslim,gobar and gomutra was not the only govt. agenda,A young educated prime minister thought about providing quality education to selected poor and remote students,who otherwise could not have afforded it.and this is how JNVs came to existence. Every year,Navodaya Vidhyalaya Samiti conducts entrance exam for class 5 students all over India.Exam forms are available at all govt.schoola and panchayat samiti es and can be submitted in some selected govt schools for free. Samity conduct a selection test around early february and declare result well before session starts for class 6.This is the main and only procedure to get in Navodaya in class 6 . Some students leaves for various reasons,so there are few vacancy in higher classes,which samiti advertise time to time in newspapers ,and are filled by taking test in respective Navodaya Vidhyalaya. ",
