            "answer_text": "Jawahar Navodaya Vidyalaya provides admissions to the students who are coming in 6th, 9th and 11th class. To get admission in 6th class, a test is conducted named as JNVST(Jawahar Navodaya Vidyalaya Selection Test) at many centres. Thousands of students give this test and few are selected. In 9th class also JNVST for 9th class is conducted. Admissions in 11th class are merit-based. It means that students are selected on the basis of their 10th class marks. Thanks S-am ",
